cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL 

The paper discusses the efficient analysis of parametric Markov chains, which involves algorithms, data structures, and engineering. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Among these, cs.LO and cs.DS are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the algorithmic and data structure aspects of the paper. cs.AI is also a possibility, as the paper discusses the use of parametric Markov chains in various applications, which could be seen as an AI-related topic. cs.SE and cs.PL are less likely, as they are more focused on software development and programming languages, respectively, which are not the main focus of the paper.
